name: B&B  "Casa Valeria"  (Wifi free)
description: Casa Valeria is equipped with: private bathroom,hairdryer,heating,AC, free WiFi and offers a great breakfast. At Vomero there is: Villa Floridiana,Castel S.Elmo,La Certosa di S.Martino and thanks to 3 funiculars, 1 Metro connects all the other neighborhoods
neighborhood_overview:
El Vomero
Il Vomero is one of the quietest and most exclusive neighborhoods in Naples, once a green hill where Neapolitan nobles had a villa in the countryside or cultivated lands.
Currently there are numerous buildings and buildings at Vomero, but you can still see many delicious Liberty-style buildings and even a few villas.
The green lung of Vomero is Villa Floridiana, a beautiful park inside which is the National Museum of Ceramics. Also to visit are Castel Sant 'Elmo, where numerous events take place, and the Certosa di San Martino overlooking the hill from its summit and where the famous Neapolitan Presepial Museum is located. The Vomero is also a place where you can shop in the pedestrian area of Via Scarlatti, with its main Piazza Vanvitelli, home to shows and fashion shows and concerts. You can access the Vomero through the brand new hilly subway and the three funiculars.
Here are numerous places where you can eat typical Neapolitan things at a low cost

Hi my name is Luca and I am the owner of Hostel of the Sun in Naples, Italy.  I am both passionate about travelling and meeting other travellers and me and the other staff here at the hostel are here 24/7 to help make your time in Naples unique. 

The Hostel has been open now for over ten years and in this time we've honed our hospitality skills. host_about:
Hi my name is Luca and I am the owner of Hostel of the Sun in Naples, Italy.  I am both passionate about travelling and meeting other travellers and me and the other staff here at the hostel are here 24/7 to help make your time in Naples unique. 

The Hostel has been open now for over ten years and in this time we've honed our hospitality skills.  We're here to show you the best this beautiful city has to offer; whether that be the food, nightlife, sightseeing highlights or Naples' amazing surroundings. We're happiest when a guest leaves loving this city just as much as we do!

We have THE BEST location for a tourist in the city; opposite the main port for ferries to the Bay's Islands Ischia, Capri and Procida, a 500m walk to the bus depo for buses direct to Pompei and the Amalfi Coast and an easy tram or bus ride from the Naples Main Station.  We're just around the corner from the main square Piazza Plebiscito and a short walk to the Historical Center for the best Pizza in the world!!!

description:
Isa Guest Rooms welcomes you to its apartment. It has 4 rooms, to satisfy the needs of all the guests. Isabella and Antonio will be happy to welcome you and make your stay unique. Room rate includes breakfast (Neapolitan style).
All four rooms are equipped with private bathroom with shower, private balcony and all kinds of comforts: Wi-Fi, fridge, LCD TV, air conditioners and heating.
neighborhood_overview:
Mergellina is one of the nicest areas in Naples. Virgil lived here, looking at the poetic and picturesque coasts of Vesuvius and Sorrento. He inspired Dante, Boccaccio and Petrarca. Located in the Chiaia district, at the foot of the Posillipo hill, it stretched around the harbor, a fishermen's time and today mainly tourist and the church of S. Maria del Porto founded by Jacopo Sannazzaro in 1524.
Mergellina has always been decanted for its beauty and panorama. Over the centuries it has been transformed to leave the place at the famous seafront of via Caracciolo. It is within walking distance of the symbols of the Parthenon culture: the Castel dell'Ovo, Piazza del Plebiscito, the Molo Beverello, the Pier of Mergellina. From the Pier of Mergellina and from Beverello Pier, the main links to the islands of the Gulf: Capri, Ischia, Procida and also the main destinations of the Amalfi and Sorrento coast.
Naples and its districts are able to show different souls to the most attenti

name: B&B la casa di Bruno Stanza Blu
description: Classic and elegant decor, breathtaking views of Castel sant'elmo
neighborhood_overview:
Welcome to Naples! Located on the west coast of southern Italy, Naples is a fascinating city that is full of history. With its narrow streets, ancient palaces, and artistic treasures, it's a place you can't help but explore during your stay.

Our property is close to several points of interest that we recommend you visit. One of these is the Basilica of San Giovanni Maggiore, an important place of worship with beautiful architecture. You can admire its frescoes and discover its thousand-year history.

Another interesting stop is the Church of San Marcellino e Festo, a Gothic church dating back to the 13th century. Inside, you can admire the frescoes and works of art that adorn its walls.

If you are passionate about art history, you can't miss the Statue of the Nile God. This Roman statue, located in the National Archaeological Museum of Naples, represents the Egyptian god Nile and is considered one of the most important works of antiquity.
